-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-American Express, eBay, Dynegy
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 02:37AM EDT
-- None



July 14 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including American Express, eBay and Dynegy, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * American Express <AXP.N>: Credit Suisse raises target price to $85 from $75 * eBay Inc <EBAY.O>: Pacific Crest cuts to sector perform * Dynegy <DYN.N>: ISI Group cuts to neutral rating  Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * Aercap Holdings <AER.N>: Credit Suisse raises target price to $48 from $46; outperform * American Express <AXP.N>: Credit Suisse raises target price to $85 from $75; underperform * Capital One Financial <COF.N>: Credit Suisse raises target price to $90 from $72; neutral  * Discover Financial Services <DFS.N>: Credit Suisse raises target price to $71 from $62 * Dynegy <DYN.N>: ISI Group cuts to neutral, price target to $35 * eBay Inc <EBAY.O>: Pacific Crest cuts to sector perform * St. Jude Medical <STJ.N>: Leerink raises target price to $80 from $75; rating outperform